Not that having the new “you” just crushed all your other issues… OK that is significant – but similar to me – that’s not “the” event. Now – there were a lot of big events before 2014, but looking back I feel much more the impact that that period of time (8 years) made.

“A rock and prosperity is on the tip of my tongue just living the season. But I think we’ve outdone ourselves.”

STEF
It is welcome news that Chadbenson Podcast is blasting into the stratosphere. And it is intriguing that the podcasters (a chorus, if I may use that verb) were stressing the third year as being the most important/fun/explosive. I pose the question: Why does this third year seem to be the most enjoyable, prolific period for all of us podcasters? Is it age? Wisdom? Spiritual ascendence? Sharecropping? Respect? Envy? Are we Jews that finally got invited into the neighborhood? Lambda Lambda Lambda is suddenly after our girls? Are we drinking blunts and pretending to be weedsmokers? Unfortunately I can’t answer this one yet – because I’m still perpetually stuck on Episode 1 !

STONEWALL
